<paragraph id="8BA136D1FF977667FF3AD7B84B3CF6EF" blockId="74.[145,264,992,1013]" box="[145,264,992,1013]" pageId="74" pageNumber="491">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FF977667FF3AD7B84B3CF6EF" box="[145,264,992,1013]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="491">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA136D1FF977667FF3AD0464834F052" blockId="74.[145,762,1054,1352]" pageId="74" pageNumber="491">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FF977667FF3AD0464AEFF129" box="[145,219,1054,1075]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="491">Males:</emphasis>
A depression between protegulum and tegulum is unique for this species. Further distinguished from most 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D52FF977667FF7ED0044B95F168" box="[213,417,1116,1138]" pageId="74" pageNumber="491">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FF977667FF7ED0044B74F16B" box="[213,320,1116,1137]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="491">Mitrager</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
by a prosoma with a hump comprising the PME, and an ocular region bearing dense setae. Distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D52FF977667FDEBD0C248F2F1B4" authorityName="COMB." authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Tanasevitch" baseAuthorityYear="1998" box="[576,710,1177,1199]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Mitrager" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="74" pageNumber="491" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="falcifer">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FF977667FDEBD0C248F2F1B4" box="[576,710,1177,1199]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="491">M. falcifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D52FF977667FD71D0C24B28F1D7" authorityName="Lin &amp; Lopardo &amp; Uhl" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Tanasevitch" baseAuthorityYear="2015" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Mitrager" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="74" pageNumber="491" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="falciferoides">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FF977667FD71D0C24B28F1D7" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="491">M. falciferoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and ‘ 
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FF977667FEF2D0E04B4AF1D7" box="[345,382,1208,1229]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="491">Oe.</emphasis>
’ 
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FF977667FE21D0E0489EF1D7" box="[394,682,1208,1229]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="491">
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D52FF977667FE21D0E04833F1D7" authority="Lin &amp; Lopardo &amp; Uhl, 2022" authorityName="Lin &amp; Lopardo &amp; Uhl" authorityYear="2022" box="[394,519,1208,1229]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Oedothorax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="74" pageNumber="491" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="meghalaya" status="incertae sedis">meghalaya</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25957B8FF977667FDA4D0E0489EF1D7" box="[527,682,1208,1229]" pageId="74" pageNumber="491">incertae sedis</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
by the smaller hump elevation; from 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D52FF977667FE5FD08F4893F1F1" baseAuthorityName="Tanasevitch" baseAuthorityYear="1998" box="[500,679,1238,1260]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Mitrager" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="74" pageNumber="491" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="malearmata">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FF977667FE5FD08F4893F1F1" box="[500,679,1238,1260]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="491">M. malearmata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the longer spike prolateral to the palpal tibia prolateral apophysis; and from 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D52FF977667FE26D14C4823F033" baseAuthorityName="Tanasevitch" baseAuthorityYear="1998" box="[397,535,1300,1321]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Mitrager" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="74" pageNumber="491" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="modesta">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FF977667FE26D14C4823F033" box="[397,535,1300,1321]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="491">M. modesta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D52FF977667FD8DD14C48A8F033" authorityName="Lin &amp; Lopardo &amp; Uhl" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Tanasevitch" baseAuthorityYear="2015" box="[550,668,1300,1321]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Mitrager" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="74" pageNumber="491" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lopchu">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FF977667FD8DD14C48A8F033" box="[550,668,1300,1321]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="491">M. lopchu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D52FF977667FD70D14C4AD4F052" authorityName="COMB." authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Tanasevitch" baseAuthorityYear="2015" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Mitrager" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="74" pageNumber="491" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rustica">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FF977667FD70D14C4AD4F052" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="491">M. rustica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the smaller body size.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA136D1FF977667FF3AD12A4B2DF09D" blockId="74.[145,281,1394,1415]" box="[145,281,1394,1415]" pageId="74" pageNumber="491">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FF977667FF3AD12A4B2DF09D" box="[145,281,1394,1415]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="491">Description:</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA136D1FF977667FF3AD1F04F46F792" blockId="74.[145,761,1448,1868]" lastBlockId="74.[809,1426,197,648]" pageId="74" pageNumber="491">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FF977667FF3AD1F04B60F0A7" box="[145,340,1448,1469]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="491">
Male (
<typeStatus id="54A58873FF977667FF74D1F04B72F0A7" box="[223,326,1448,1469]" pageId="74" pageNumber="491">holotype</typeStatus>
):
</emphasis>
Total length: 2.40. Prosoma: 1.01 long, 0.77 wide, PME- and postocular region slightly elevated, with one strong seta at peak of elevation pointing forwards, interocular region with strong setae pointing upwards (
<figureCitation id="13252A54FF977667FE1FD27A4828F322" box="[436,540,1570,1592]" captionStart="Figure 38" captionStartId="70.[145,223,1426,1448]" captionTargetBox="[148,1428,198,1384]" captionTargetId="figure-25@70.[145,1431,195,1387]" captionTargetPageId="70" captionText="Figure 38. Male prosomal morphology of Clade 55 in Figure 3, lateral.A, Mitrager hirsuta (Wunderlich, 1974) (Wunderlich, 1974, fig. 8). B, M. clypeellum (Tanasevitch, 1998) (traced from photograph). C, M. elongata (Wunderlich, 1974) (Wunderlich, 1974, fig. 13). D, M. cornuta (Tanasevitch, 2015) (Tanasevitch, 2015, fig. 16). E, M. villosa (Tanasevitch, 2015) (Tanasevitch, 2015, fig. 89). F, M. angela (Tanasevitch, 1998) (Tanasevitch, 1998a, fig. 14). G, M. coronata (Tanasevitch, 1998) (Tanasevitch, 1998a, fig. 6). H, M. sexoculorum (Tanasevitch, 1998) (Tanasevitch, 1998a, fig. 19). I, M. globiceps (Thaler, 1987) (traced from photograph). J, M.lineata (Wunderlich, 1974) (traced from photograph).K, M. dismodicoides (Wunderlich, 1974) (traced from photograph). L, M. tholusa (Tanasevitch, 1998) (Tanasevitch, 1998a, fig. 24). M, M. lucida (Wunderlich, 1974) (Wunderlich, 1974, fig. 30). N, M. sexoculata (Wunderlich, 1974) (traced from photograph). O. M. noordami van Helsdingen, 1985 (van Helsdingen, 1985, fig. 1). P, M. unicolor (Wunderlich, 1974) (traced from photograph). Q, M. rustica (Tanasevitch, 2015) (Tanasevitch, 2015, fig. 75). R, M. assueta (Tanasevitch, 1998) (Tanasevitch, 1998a, fig. 1). S, M. malearmata (Tanasevitch, 1998) (Tanasevitch, 1998a, fig. 50). T, M. savigniformis (Tanasevitch, 1998) (Tanasevitch, 1998a, fig. 40). U, M. falcifer (Tanasevitch, 1998) (Tanasevitch, 1998a, fig. 46). V, M. modesta (Tanasevitch, 1998) (Tanasevitch, 1998a, fig. 36). W, M. lopchu (Tanasevitch, 2015) (traced from photograph). X, M. falciferoides (Tanasevitch, 2015) (Tanasevitch, 2015, fig. 35)." pageId="74" pageNumber="491">Figs 38R</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13252A54FF977667FD81D27B486DF322" box="[554,601,1571,1592]" captionStart="Figure 43" captionStartId="76.[145,225,997,1019]" captionTargetBox="[209,1359,197,956]" captionTargetId="figure-412@76.[207,1362,195,957]" captionTargetPageId="76" captionText="Figure 43. Interocular strong setae, lateral view. A, ‘Oedothorax’ meghalaya (Tanasevitch, 2015). B, Mitrager assueta (Tanasevitch, 1998). Scale bars 0.1 mm." pageId="74" pageNumber="491">43B</figureCitation>
). Eyes: AME- AME: 0.04, AME width: 0.04, AME-ALE: 0.03, ALE width: 0.08, ALE-PLE: 0, PLE width: 0.07, PLE-PME: 0.07, PME width: 0.07, PME-PME: 0.11. Clypeus: not hirsute. Sternum: 0.59 long, 0.57 wide. Chelicerae: stridulatory striae imbricated, rows widely and evenly spaced (
<figureCitation id="13252A54FF977667FF5BD2824B66F3F5" box="[240,338,1754,1776]" captionStart="Figure 39" captionStartId="71.[163,241,1801,1823]" captionTargetBox="[165,1432,197,1757]" captionTargetId="figure-26@71.[163,1446,195,1762]" captionTargetPageId="71" captionText="Figure 39. Male chelicerae, stridulatory striae on lateral side. A, Mitrager hirsuta. B, M. clypeellum. C, M. elongata. D, M. cornuta. E, M. villosa. F, M. angela. G, M. coronata. H, M. sexoculorum. I, M. globiceps. J, M. lineata. K, M. dismodicoides. L, M. tholusa. M, M. lucida. N, M. sexoculata. O, M. noordami. P,M. unicolor. Q, M. rustica. R, M. assueta. S, M. savigniformis. T, M. falcifer. U, M. modesta. V, M. falciferoides. Scale bars 0.05 mm." pageId="74" pageNumber="491">Fig. 39R</figureCitation>
). Legs: Tm I: 0.56. Pedipalp: patella prolateral proximal vertical macrosetae present; tibia with one prolateral, two retrolateral trichobothria; TPS scaly, retrolaterally pointed; TPA absent; TRA bent retrolaterally; PC short, base not visible from dorsal view, distal setae close to distal clasp, distal clasp without striae, directed retrolaterally (
<figureCitation id="13252A54FF977667FA8FD55A4FB7F40D" box="[1316,1411,258,280]" captionStart="Figure 42" captionStartId="75.[163,241,1121,1143]" captionTargetBox="[166,1443,198,1079]" captionTargetId="figure-323@75.[163,1449,195,1082]" captionTargetPageId="75" captionText="Figure 42. Mitrager assueta (Tanasevitch, 1998). A–D, male right palp, images flipped horizontally. A, retrolateral view. B, prolateral view. C, dorsal view. D, ventral view. E, male spinnerets. Scale bars 0.1 mm." pageId="74" pageNumber="491">Fig. 42A</figureCitation>
); T without papillae; PT with long papillae, a depression between T and PT creates a discontinuous appearance from lateral view (
<figureCitation id="13252A54FF977667FBABD5064E56F469" box="[1024,1122,350,372]" captionStart="Figure 42" captionStartId="75.[163,241,1121,1143]" captionTargetBox="[166,1443,198,1079]" captionTargetId="figure-323@75.[163,1449,195,1082]" captionTargetPageId="75" captionText="Figure 42. Mitrager assueta (Tanasevitch, 1998). A–D, male right palp, images flipped horizontally. A, retrolateral view. B, prolateral view. C, dorsal view. D, ventral view. E, male spinnerets. Scale bars 0.1 mm." pageId="74" pageNumber="491">Fig. 42D</figureCitation>
); MSA present (
<figureCitation id="13252A54FF977667FA8BD5064FB6F469" box="[1312,1410,350,372]" captionStart="Figure 42" captionStartId="75.[163,241,1121,1143]" captionTargetBox="[166,1443,198,1079]" captionTargetId="figure-323@75.[163,1449,195,1082]" captionTargetPageId="75" captionText="Figure 42. Mitrager assueta (Tanasevitch, 1998). A–D, male right palp, images flipped horizontally. A, retrolateral view. B, prolateral view. C, dorsal view. D, ventral view. E, male spinnerets. Scale bars 0.1 mm." pageId="74" pageNumber="491">Fig. 42D</figureCitation>
); DSA not pointed, not retrolaterally curved (
<figureCitation id="13252A54FF977667FA89D5254FB6F488" box="[1314,1410,381,403]" captionStart="Figure 42" captionStartId="75.[163,241,1121,1143]" captionTargetBox="[166,1443,198,1079]" captionTargetId="figure-323@75.[163,1449,195,1082]" captionTargetPageId="75" captionText="Figure 42. Mitrager assueta (Tanasevitch, 1998). A–D, male right palp, images flipped horizontally. A, retrolateral view. B, prolateral view. C, dorsal view. D, ventral view. E, male spinnerets. Scale bars 0.1 mm." pageId="74" pageNumber="491">Fig. 42A</figureCitation>
); EM flat, anterior margin without obvious papillae, exceeds ARP (
<figureCitation id="13252A54FF977667FC7AD5E24E02F4D5" box="[977,1078,442,464]" captionStart="Figure 42" captionStartId="75.[163,241,1121,1143]" captionTargetBox="[166,1443,198,1079]" captionTargetId="figure-323@75.[163,1449,195,1082]" captionTargetPageId="75" captionText="Figure 42. Mitrager assueta (Tanasevitch, 1998). A–D, male right palp, images flipped horizontally. A, retrolateral view. B, prolateral view. C, dorsal view. D, ventral view. E, male spinnerets. Scale bars 0.1 mm." pageId="74" pageNumber="491">Fig. 42D</figureCitation>
); ARP pointed, angled at tip; LER with striae on distal margin, extended dorsal to E; VRP absent; TP round at tip, ventro-posterior area with round extension (
<figureCitation id="13252A54FF977667FBC3D64E4EF3F731" box="[1128,1223,534,556]" captionStart="Figure 42" captionStartId="75.[163,241,1121,1143]" captionTargetBox="[166,1443,198,1079]" captionTargetId="figure-323@75.[163,1449,195,1082]" captionTargetPageId="75" captionText="Figure 42. Mitrager assueta (Tanasevitch, 1998). A–D, male right palp, images flipped horizontally. A, retrolateral view. B, prolateral view. C, dorsal view. D, ventral view. E, male spinnerets. Scale bars 0.1 mm." pageId="74" pageNumber="491">Fig. 42B</figureCitation>
); E retrolaterally spiral, anterior margin at base slightly wavy (
<figureCitation id="13252A54FF977667FA8DD66D4FB7F750" box="[1318,1411,565,587]" captionStart="Figure 42" captionStartId="75.[163,241,1121,1143]" captionTargetBox="[166,1443,198,1079]" captionTargetId="figure-323@75.[163,1449,195,1082]" captionTargetPageId="75" captionText="Figure 42. Mitrager assueta (Tanasevitch, 1998). A–D, male right palp, images flipped horizontally. A, retrolateral view. B, prolateral view. C, dorsal view. D, ventral view. E, male spinnerets. Scale bars 0.1 mm." pageId="74" pageNumber="491">Fig. 42B</figureCitation>
). Opisthosoma: dorsal pattern see 
<figureCitation id="13252A54FF977667FB06D60C4F39F773" box="[1197,1293,596,618]" captionStart="Figure 40" captionStartId="72.[143,221,1340,1362]" captionTargetBox="[147,1426,197,1296]" captionTargetId="figure-173@72.[145,1428,195,1301]" captionTargetPageId="72" captionText="Figure 40. Opisthosoma, dorsal view. A–L, N–Y, male; D, female. A, Mitrager hirsuta (Wunderlich, 1974). B, M. clypeellum (Tanasevitch, 1998). C, M. elongata (Wunderlich, 1974). D, M. cornuta (Tanasevitch, 2015). E, M. villosa (Tanasevitch, 2015). F,M. angela (Tanasevitch, 1998). G, M. coronata (Tanasevitch, 1998). H, M. sexoculorum (Tanasevitch, 1998). I, M. globiceps (Thaler, 1987). J, M. lineata (Wunderlich, 1974). K, M. dismodicoides (Wunderlich, 1974). L, M. tholusa (Tanasevitch, 1998), holotype. M, ‘M. tholusa’, paratype (not conspecific with holotype). N, M. lucida (Wunderlich, 1974). O, M. sexoculata (Wunderlich, 1974). P,. M. noordami van Helsdingen, 1985. Q, M. unicolor (Wunderlich, 1974). R, M. rustica (Tanasevitch, 2015). S, M. assueta (Tanasevitch, 1998). T, M. savigniformis (Tanasevitch, 1998), paratype. U, M. savigniformis, holotype. V, M. falcifer (Tanasevitch, 1998). W, M. modesta (Tanasevitch, 1998). X, M. lopchu (Tanasevitch, 2015). Y, M. falciferoides (Tanasevitch, 2015). Scale bars 0.1 mm." pageId="74" pageNumber="491">Fig. 40S</figureCitation>
; PMS with mAP, AC absent; PLS with triad, one AC (
<figureCitation id="13252A54FF977667FAAFD62A4F57F79D" box="[1284,1379,626,648]" captionStart="Figure 42" captionStartId="75.[163,241,1121,1143]" captionTargetBox="[166,1443,198,1079]" captionTargetId="figure-323@75.[163,1449,195,1082]" captionTargetPageId="75" captionText="Figure 42. Mitrager assueta (Tanasevitch, 1998). A–D, male right palp, images flipped horizontally. A, retrolateral view. B, prolateral view. C, dorsal view. D, ventral view. E, male spinnerets. Scale bars 0.1 mm." pageId="74" pageNumber="491">Fig. 42E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA136D1FF977667FC82D6E94EAFF7FF" blockId="74.[809,1424,689,742]" pageId="74" pageNumber="491">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FF977667FC82D6E949C4F7DC" box="[809,1008,689,710]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="491">
Male (
<typeStatus id="54A58873FF977667FCDDD6E949D6F7DC" box="[886,994,689,710]" pageId="74" pageNumber="491">paratype</typeStatus>
):
</emphasis>
Total length: 2.39. Prosoma: 1.05 long, 0.86 wide. Legs: Tm I: 0.59.
</paragraph>
